    "causal_summary": "The spec-memory daemon supervisor decides a daemon is healthy from process liveness (`process.kill(pid,0)`) plus socket-file existence, never a request/response probe. When a daemon is alive but its event loop is wedged (it accepts the socket connection but never services requests), the supervisor adopts it \"instead of reaping\" and bridges clients into a dead end — `ECONNREFUSED` forever, with no path to self-recovery. A real incident proved this: one daemon spun a full core for ~4 hours while every client call failed. This packet makes the stale-reclaim adoption path **deep-probe before adopting**, and reap+respawn on a failed probe.",
